body:
Okay, rebasing `go` against `master` and then `go_updates` against `go` kept giving me merge conflicts when I would push here. I think because I wasn't able to push to `origin/go`.

I've just merged in master.

We could do this in two steps if someone who can push `origin/go` can step in. First step: rebase `go` against `master`, and then I can apply these last two commits from myself.
